text: Douglas McClelland (born 5 August 1926) is an Australian politician. He was elected to the Australian Senate as a member of the Australian Labor Party at the 1961 election, representing New South Wales. He left the Senate 1987. From 1983 to 1987, he was President of the Senate. ==References== Category:1926 births Category:Living people Category:Presidents of the Australian Senate Category:Politicians from New South Wales
